          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "<h2><strong>How to Apply Perfume for Maximum Impact</strong></h2>",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_cw6VG6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Selecting the right fragrance is only the first step. Even the best perfume for men won’t deliver if not applied correctly. Learning to do it right is a skill and art in itself that many ignore.</p><p><strong>Target Pulse Points</strong>: Spray behind the ears, on the wrists and at the base of the throat. These areas radiate heat and help diffuse the scent.</p><p><strong>Don't Rub</strong>: Rubbing breaks down the fragrance molecules. Let the perfume settle naturally.</p><p><strong>Layer Wisely</strong>: Start with an unscented moisturiser to help lock in the fragrance.</p><p><strong>Storage Tips</strong>: Keep your perfume in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight.</p><p>Applied right, your perfume becomes a part of your presence. It delivers the lasting duration it is meant for.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
